17/07/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Heavy floods in Bulgaria and Romania have killed 20 people and caused considerable damage to infrastructure and homes, according to reports in Sofia and Bucharest on Friday (15 July).
In all, 15 people died in different incidents in Romania, where more than 12,000 were forced to evacuate their homes.
In Bulgaria, flood-related losses are estimated at 100m euros.
Both countries have asked the EU and NATO for assistance.
(AP, bTV, Rompres - 15/07/05)
